Package server.models

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    Actuator
    An actuator is a connected object managed by the server and performing physical actions according to it.
    Ambience  
    AtomicAction
    An action is a message sent by the server to the actuators which needs to react according to it.
    Behaviour
    A behaviour is a comportment of an actuator depending on environment variables.
    Command
    A command is the information about the possible values (continuous or discrete) an actuator can receive to perform one action
    ComplexAction
    A complex action is a collection of atomic actions.
    ExternalActor  
    History  
    Right  
    Role  
    Sensor
    A sensor is a connected object in charge of sending useful changes about environment variables to the server.
